<TEXT>
a vietnamese man is thrown from a moving 
train a factory fires foreigners to trim its payroll young toughs 
club a kurd unconcious racism is increasing in east germany 
blessed with new freedom and german pride but plagued by a 
crashing economy and competition for scarce jobs east germans have 
become openly hostile to foreign minorities 
i am ashamed of the behavior of the east german people said 
horst kinitz chief of the nations employment agency 
organized bands of neonazi skinheads radical youths with 
shaved heads and aggressive attitudes have attacked asians and 
africans who make up the bulk of east germanys foreign workers 
about 80000 vietnamese angolans mozambicans and cubans have 
been working in east germany under arrangements made with those 
countries by the former communist government 
im very afraid said ngo manh long a vietnamese worker in 
an east berlin textile factory the gangs make problems for us 
the german people are angry we are here 
few such incidents were apparent under the communists who 
maintained order with a suffocating internal security system 
rapid economic and social upheaval and east germanys emergence 
as a central european crossroads have left its people dizzy with 
change after four decades of isolationism 
lt joachim crannich of the national police said the agency 
recorded 32 cases of violence against foreigners in the first half 
of 1990 but added the actual count probably was much higher 
you have to see it in the context of our social changes he 
said with the move toward democracy and introduction of the free 
market many people are anxious if youre an east german and you 
lose your job but you see a foreigner keep his job that creates a 
certain frustation 
among the incidents this year 
skinheads attacked a grooup of vietnamese on a train from 
eisenach to berlin 
a vietnamese was pushed off a train and seriously injured in 
wittenburg 
in leipzig skinheads attacked african students shouting 
racial epithets and foreigners out 
a dozen skinheads covered a vietnamese man with spray paint in 
rudolstadt an iraqi kurd said young toughs jumped him pulled his 
jacket over his head and beat him unconcious 
i felt like a jew during the third reich he said 
many people blame organized radical rightwing groups such as 
the national alternative for such attacks the group denies it 
juergen helfricht spokesman for the interior ministry said 
there was no proof the national alternative was involved in 
anything illegal so police had no grounds to move against it 
experts say the skinheads despite the attention they draw are 
only the violent fringe of a broader problem 
the sensitivity in the east german population about racism is 
abominably low said annetta kahane the east berlin city 
official who deals with foreigners concerns its going to take 
a long time until it reaches the same level as west germany and 
its not very good in west germany 
factories have become bastions of racism east germany switched 
to a free market and merged its economy with west germanys on july 
1 a prelude to reunification in december 
unemployment is growing and there are numerous reports of 
foreign workers being fired first as businesses trim payrolls 
volker daehne deputy chief of the east german employment 
authority said he had 296 documented cases since july 1 of foreign 
workers being fired illegally 
its shameful to bring foreigners into this country and then 
fire them at will he said 
manh the vietnamese worker is employed by an east berlin maker 
of mens clothing called becon classic a former state concern now 
operating independently he said there is open hostility in the 
plant 
a complaint filed with the east berlin government by vietnamese 
workers says rents have tripled in housing supplied by becon and 
two other factories east germans are protected from extreme rent 
increases 
manh said he and eight other vietnamese were living in a 
oneroom apartment and had paid the equivalent of 19 a month each 
but the rent more than tripled in july 
veronika arendtrojah a west berlin lawyer representing 
vietnamese at becon classic said she would file suit to block the 
increases 
plant spokesman wolfgang boerner said there were no plans to 
fire foreigners he said rents had to be raised because subsidizing 
them was a burden on the company 
</TEXT>
