the domestic textile industry and its workers 
are portraying themselves as sacrificial lambs in the 
administrations jockeying to reduce foreign trade barriers to us 
exports 
casting itself as a victim is nothing new for an industry that 
has lost 30 percent of the american textile and clothing market and 
about 400000 jobs to foreigners in the 1980s alone 
