prices dropped sharply today on the tokyo stock 
exchange reflecting wide uncertainty about the longterm effects 
on oil prices and interest rates of japanese sanctions against iraq 
meanwhile the dollar closed slightly up against the japanese yen 
the nikkei stock average of 225 selected issues closed at 
2859953 points down 91623 points or 31 percent on trading of 
an estimated 330 million shares the index lost 72942 points 
friday the day after iraqs invasion 
the index fell 110669 points or 37 percent in morning 
trading in response to the government announcement sunday night 
that tokyo would ban all oil imports from iraq and kuwait and 
japanese exports to the two countries 
