the south african government and 
the african national congress began talks today to try to clear the 
way for fullscale constitutional negotiations on ending 
whiteminority rule 
president fw de klerk and anc leader nelson mandela leading 
fiveman delegations arrived separately at a state mansion on the 
outskirts of pretoria neither leader said anything to waiting 
jouranlists as their convoys swept through the gates 
all leading south african newspapers carried reports sunday that 
the anc was expected to declare a ceasefire if there was progress 
in todays talks an agreement would clear the way for full talks 
probably early next year according to political sources 
the news reports said the two sides expect to reach agreement on 
releasing political prisoners and allowing return of political 
exiles to south africa the government is also expected to meet anc 
demands for a review of security laws that have been used to 
suppress political activity 
the government would like to see immediate progresss on the 
negotiations it would like to see negotiations take off but 
