struggle 
the ancs armed struggle virtually collapsed because of internal 
problems the drying up of support following the fall of communist 
regimes in eastern europe and the superiority of the south african 
military 
but mandela has refused to formally renounce the armed struggle 
despite intense pressure from the government and many western 
