<TEXT>
the red cross sometimes worries more about its 
image than about emergency relief sending agency camera crews in 
ahead of aid workers a newspaper concluded after analyzing 200 
disasters over the past five years 
a ninemonth investigation by the pittsburgh press showed that 
in some cases the red cross lived up to its promise to deliver 
help quickly fairly and compassionately 
but in others there were widespread deficiencies 
the problems included delays of up to six days before enough 
trained workers arrived at a disaster site a lack of cooperation 
with local agencies and an emphasis on getting favorable publicity 
to help raise money 
the paper in a series that began in sundays newspaper also 
said the charity does not always spend all money donated for a 
specific disaster on that disaster 
the red cross is by far the nations largest recipient of 
disaster contributions totaling 175 million last year however 
the newspaper concluded that other groups primarily the salvation 
army and other national church groups usually arrive at disaster 
sites first and stay longer 
agency officials said it was unfair to criticize the red cross 
because of highly publicized shortcomings following hurricane hugo 
and the northern california earthquake last year 
its absurd to look at last falls hurricane and earthquake 
and say the red cross cant do the job the red cross may have had 
a few little problems but we were dealing with two unprecedented 
disasters said barbara lohman a national red cross spokeswoman 
in washington dc 
if you want to be fair and get an accurate picture look at 
the hundreds of other disasters that we worked on and youll find 
that the red cross performance was almost flawless she told the 
newspaper 
the red cross unique operating position was created in 1900 
when congress passed a law making it the only volunteer agency 
required to aid victims of disaster it was founded by civil war 
nurse clara barton in 1881 
today funded almost totally by donations from the american 
public the 12 billion operation promises immediate response to a 
disaster with food and shelter medical care clothing temporary 
housing and other basic needs 
to raise money the red cross stresses promoting its image even 
in the early hours of a disaster according to the newspaper report 
two of the four names posted on the nightly callout roster at 
national headquarters in washington dc those people to be 
notified in case of a major disaster are fundraisers 
