the report was continuing and should be completed by early next 
month 
in 1987 the last year for which data is available the overall 
infant mortality rate for the united states was 101 deaths in the 
first year of life for every 1000 births the rate was 179 for 
blacks and 86 for whites 
in the 1970s the public health service set a goal of reducing 
the rate to nine by 1990 and said no racial group should have a 
rate exceeding 12 
