prime targets for international oil sanctions against iraq the 
middle east economic survey wrote 
but it should be remembered on the one hand that turkey gets a 
substantial part of its own oil supply through the iraqi pipeline 
and on the other that any action by saudi arabia to interfere with 
the terminals by means of us naval power could also be a tricky 
exercise the newsletter wrote 
the upshot of all this is that although effective global oil 
sanctions would undoubtedly cripple iraq they would be difficult 
to implement and administer in practice it said 
turkish officials however said the decision to close the 
pipeline through their country would not affect turkish purchases 
of iraqi oil expected to account for about 40 percent of turkeys 
oil needs this year 
