under pressure from saddam to restrict production in order to 
push up oil prices 
now the normal pattern of oil supply and trade have been 
radically distorted and crisis buying has already lifted prices to 
somewhere around the 21abarrel opec basket range it wrote 
it said unless conditions return to normal pretty soon the 
damage to the agreement and perhaps opec itself may prove 
beyond repair 
the middle east economic survey said this brought to mind the 
two previous occasions in the past 20 years when the oil market was 
convulsed by political upheavals in 197374 when the arabs imposed 
an oil embargo during the arabisraeli war and the 197981 price 
explosion 
those oil shocks especially the second one drove the world 
into economic recession 
