cleanup crews sprayed some 150 pounds of oileating bacteria on 
marshlands that cannot be safely reached with skimming vessels 
in the process begun last week the naturally occurring microbes 
reduce the oil to a fatty substance that sinks and is eaten by fish 
this is different from oil on rocks or oil in open waters 
said texas water commission chairman bj buck wynne this is 
on a living organic system and its absolutely the most sensitive 
place it can be 
