<TEXT>
an earthquake sharply jolted a northern 
iranian town on monday more than month after a quake killed 40000 
people in the region there was no immediate report of damage or 
injuries 
the islamic republic news agency monitored in nicosia said the 
temblor struck rudbar in northern gilan province at 1255 pm it 
measured 45 on the richter scale of ground motion 
it said more than 2000 quakes have shaken the region since the 
devastating june 21 earthquake which registered 73 on the richter 
scale that quake also left 60000 injured and rendered half 
million homeless irovinces of gilan and zanjan 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one on the northern pf 65 
an earthquake of 4 on the richter scale can cause moderate 
damage in the local area 5 considerable damage 6 severe damage a 
7 reading is a major earthquake capable of widespread heavy 
damage 
</TEXT>
