here are excerpts from the text of 
a joint statement tuesday by the south african government and the 
african national congress after talks on clearing the way for 
constitutional negotiations the anc agreed to halt its armed 
struggle against the white government 
the government and the anc have held discussions at the 
presidency pretoria today 6 august 1990 
the meeting has instructed the working group on political 
offenses to draw up a plan for the release of ancrelated 
prisoners and the granting of indemnity to people in a phased 
manner and to report before the end of august in the interest of 
moving as speedily as possible towards a negotiated peaceful 
political settlement and in the context of the agreements reached 
the anc announced that it was now suspending all armed actions with 
immediate effect as a result of this no further armed actions and 
related activities by the anc and its military wing umkonto we 
sizwe spear of the nation will take place 
both sides once more committed themselves to do everything in 
their power to bring about a peaceful solution as quickly as 
possible 
both delegations expressed serious concern about the general 
level of violence intimidation and unrest in the country 
especially in natal they agreed that in the context of the common 
search for peace and stability it was vital hat understanding 
should grow among all sections of the south african population that 
problems can and should be solved through negotiations both 
parties committed themselves to undertake steps and measures to 
promote and expedite the normalization and stabilization of the 
situation in line with the spirit of mutual trust obtaining among 
the leaders involved 
the government has undertaken to consider the lifting of the 
state of emergency in natal as early as possible in the light of 
positive consequences that should result from this accord 
the government will continue reviewing security legislation and 
its application in order to ensure free political activity and with 
the view to introducing amending legislation at the next session of 
parliament the minister of justice will issue a statement in this 
regard 
we are convinced that what we have agreed upon today can become 
a milestone on the road to true peace and prosperity for our 
country in this we do not pretend to be the only parties involved 
in the process of shaping the new south africa we know there are 
other parties committed to peaceful progress all of us can 
henceforth walk that road in consultation and cooperation with 
each other we call upon all those who have not yet committed 
themselves to peaceful negotiations to do so now 
against this background the way is now open to proceed towards 
negotiations on a new constitution 
