congress party said all the dead had their hands tied behind 
their backs and were either shot or cut with swords 
the killings took place in addalachena oluvil and palamuna 
villages about 125 miles east of colombo 
in other fighting at least 35 tamil rebels and three government 
security men were killed sunday the officials said 
they said 12 rebels were killed when naval gunboats destroyed a 
fiberglass dinghy trying to land on a beach of northwestern mannar 
town and two more rebels were killed in the north in a landmine 
explosion 
two policemen and a soldier were killed when rebels fired 
mortars rockets and small arms at a militaryheld fort in jaffna 
town the officials said 
helicopter gunships straffed rebel positions killing at least 
21 guerrillas they added 
about 14000 people have been killed since 1983 when tamil 
rebels took up arms claiming they were discrimnated by the 
majority sinhalese in jobs education and the use of sinhala 
language 
tamils form 18 percent of sri lankas 16 million people 
sinhalese make up roughly 75 percent and moslems 7 percent 
