economic issues would be reopened in the fourth year 
health insurance was the main issue in bargaining before the 
aug 2 agreement the news agreed to pay 300 for each employee 
with individual coverage and 600 per employee with a family plan 
into a special fund on jan 1 
that fund will be drawn down over the next two years to cover 
the employees 20 percent share of any increase in health insurance 
premiums said robert mccarthy president of local 26 of the 
newspaper guild 
