a video program that lets advertisers reach 
patients in doctor waiting rooms could be in 2500 locations by the 
end of the month its director says 
healthlink television debuted aug 1 the executive overseeing 
it david moore said tv sets and video disc players were placed in 
100 pediatricians offices in new york chicago and los angeles 
plans are to expand nationally to 5000 doctors offices by the 
end of september and 20000 by early 1991 he said 
doctors will be given a onehour program on a laserdisc that is 
to be played continuously on the tv system during the business day 
the program will focus on health care topics with up to nine 
minutes of commercials each two to four minutes long per hour 
between program segments 
healthlink television is the first of two commerciallysponsored 
video programs that are being produced for audiences in medical 
waiting rooms 
healthlink is a subsidiary of hearstabcviacom entertainment 
services a joint venture of capital citiesabc inc the hearst 
corp and viacom international inc 
