produced by whittle communications of knoxville tenn and 
debuting in october whittle is halfowned by the entertainment 
giant time warner inc 
both services are aimed principally at mothers visiting the 
doctor either for themselves or with their children 
they are the latest example of media vehicles developed to 
enable advertisers to reach narrowly defined audiences similar 
programming includes the channel one news show for teens in the 
classroom programs for women at the beauty parlor and a news show 
