keeping of paid mistresses 
the new female politicians made some inroads in their campaign 
against money politics and against a sales tax that squeezed the 
purses of japans traditional family spenders the housewives 
a record 22 women won seats in parliaments upper house in the 
july 1989 elections and 12 were elected to the lower house in 
february before the two elections about half that number were in 
parliament 
seeking to placate angry female voters prime minister toshiki 
