<TEXT>
the striking images of james lesesne wells are on view at 
hammonds house galleries in atlanta as part of the national black 
arts festival 
james lesesne wells selected works 19261988 illuminates 
the range of the artists work from the lithograph negro 
worker to the delightful nude the vamp 
wells who was born in atlanta in 1902 flourished in new york 
during the harlem renaissance and his modernist black and white 
prints established him as a leading printmaker of that period 
watercolors and drawings from the george a lucas collection are 
on show at the baltimore museum of art through oct 14 
the lucas collection known for its fine paintings by corot 
gerome pissarro and others and for its holdings of more than 
20000 french 19thcentury prints also contains an extraordinary 
group of about 100 watercolors and drawings including works by 
barye besnard daubigny daumier delacroix jongkind millet and 
whistler it is particularly strong in landscape views and scenes 
of daily life in france 
thirtyfive of the finest works most of which are rarely seen 
because of light sensitivity have been selected for the 
exhibition the lucas collection came to the maryland institute 
college of art as a gift in 1910 upon lucas death it has been on 
indefinite loan to the bma since 1933 
