<TEXT>
imagine being a foreigner and learning 
english from marlon brando 
that happened to maximilian schell 28 years ago but he still 
has managed to win an academy award and a host of other honors 
the english lessons happened when schell made the young 
lions the austrian actor had to learn his lines by phonetics 
and brando the notorious mumbler proved a big help 
it was my first experience in a hollywood movie schell 
recalls i didnt speak much english at that time and marlon was 
extremely kind to help me with the part 
whenever people say that marlon was difficult i just say with 
me hes the easiest guy in the world 
the two actors have met on occasion over the years but they 
lost touch because says schell i dont like to bother famous 
people 
they staged a reunion for the freshman in which brando 
parodies his classic don corleone portrayal in the godfather 
schell plays an expert chef who joins the mob boss in an outrageous 
scheme 
we embraced each other reports schell and we sat in the 
trailer and talked not about old times but about philosophy that 
was our favorite theme on the young lions he has become more 
of a philosopher than he was at that time 
while he has lost some of that young drive that he had he 
still is a great screen personality when hes on the screen you 
always have to find a way to stand up against him that was the 
same problem on the young lions 
i come from the classical stage hamlet and everyman and 
so forth so i was a very eloquent actor especially in my native 
tongue and marlon of course was famous for this mumble 
mumble it was fascinating because you had to listen and figure 
out what he was saying he changed the style of acting 
obviously there is a chemistry between us schell said 
even while we were shooting the freshman we talked about a 
sequel we thought it was a good idea of two guys both retired 
one in switzerland and the other in sicily they call each other 
and say are you bored 
yes 
lets do something together 
schell 59 hadnt heard of matthew broderick the college 
freshman who stumbles into the mafia but found him to be fresh 
and innovative he stands up very well 
acting was inevitable for maximilian schell whose father was a 
swiss writer and poet and mother a viennese actress four of their 
children became actors including maria who starred in the 
brothers karamazov and cimarron after the nazi invasion of 
austria in 1938 the family moved to switzerland and thats where 
max grew up attending universities at zurich and basel 
schell appeared in the classical theater and in german films 
and in 1957 he was cast as a german officer in the young lions 
along with brando montgomery clift and dean martin he managed to 
hold his own in that highpowered company and stanley kramer chose 
him to play the enigmatic defense attorney in judgment at 
nuremberg 
both schell and spencer tracy were nominated for the bestactor 
oscar for their roles in the drama of the nazi warcriminal trials 
and schell was the surprise winner he has also been nominated for 
best actor in the man in the glass booth and supporting actor 
in julia he has continued to act and direct on the stage and 
he has directed such films as marlene academy nomination for 
documentary first love and end of the game 
long one of europes most eligible bachelors he surprised his 
friends three years ago by taking a bride natalia andreichenko a 
russian actress he met while filming peter the great they have 
a daughter 18 months as well as a 7yearold son by her previous 
marriage the schells now live in los angeles 
it all goes together i think explains the philosophical 
schell you see the moment i left switzerland and went to 
germany austria london and new york i became an immigrant or 
emigrant i once said to a sculptor you know what i miss is a 
home base like a tree needs ground instead of putting a palm tree 
in the mountains or a pine in the desert 
he said no max youre a part of the future we all live on 
one planet and you represent that artist who is home everywhere 
that is a consolation for me 
marriage was also a new experience it was unavoidable when i 
was in russia playing peter the great natasha played my first 
wife she said im very angry with you because youre putting me 
into a monastery that was a line from the tv miniseries because 
she couldnt speak english 
that was a good way to introduce herself instead of sending 
her to a monastery i took her with me to hollywood when we came 
in january she said i will never leave here 
i like it too when i was a bachelor i was always going 
home you know hollywood it can be very cruel a bachelor can be 
lonely even with all the friends you have so i went back to 
europe 
now with my wife and the babies you come home you may be 
sad but she throws her arms around your neck and its all good 
</TEXT>
