<TEXT>
cynthia gregory whose exquisite 
turns and elegant phrasing helped make american ballet theatre an 
international treat in the dance world is wellsuited to the roles 
of odette and odile in swan lake 
dancing odile in the black swan pas de deux requires 32 
consecutive spins but odette the white swan is her favorite 
role while other ballerinas dance the role with melancholy and 
pathos gregory depicts strength with vulnerability and triumph 
instead of gloom 
i think im more of a woman falling in love said the 
