services or adult protective services but the agencies may refer a 
case back to the elder abuse project 
a case usually starts with project and ends with the project 
which can prosecute physical abuse as either a criminal or civil 
case confer said 
the project has three fulltime paid staff members plus an 
average of 35 volunteers a year the 82000 in salaries and other 
costs are covered within the attorney generals budget 
some people bring their complaints to the project others use 
its fraudline phone number additionally volunteers travel to 
senior centers throughout the state 
after someone contacts the project a volunteer assists in 
preparing a complaint for the projects files if the matter 
involves an individual or company licensed by a state agency the 
elder is assisted in filing a complaint with that agency 
project staff members and volunteers work to clarify issues in 
the case verify facts and obtain documentation they may consult 
experts 
the staff then may try to resolve the complaint through 
mediation or it may be referred to the appropriate division of the 
attorney generals office 
