with eight top managers to charges of falsifying safety and 
maintenance records 
us district judge i leo glasser in brooklyn released all 
eight without bail and continued proceedings to sept 12 
prosecutors allege the violations took place from july 1985 to 
october 1989 and were meant to avoid expensive flight delays and 
cancellations 
phony records allegedly were kept at kennedy international and 
la guardia airports in new york hartsfield international airport 
in atlanta and eastern headquarters in miami 
eastern and the managers were indicted july 25 on charges of 
