<TEXT>
former wall street trader salim b sandy 
lewis agreed monday to pay 475000 to settle a securities and 
exchange commission lawsuit arising from his guilty plea to 
criminal stock manipulation charges 
the sec suit filed monday in federal court alleged lewis 
violated securities laws by helping to manipulate the price of 
firemans fund corp stock in 1986 the same accusations to which 
he pleaded guilty in a criminal proceeding 
sec attorney bruce hiler said the 475000 would be placed in a 
fund and an administrator would return the money to victims of the 
scheme 
lewis 51 of short hills nj also consented to an order that 
bars him from any future securities violations 
although we believe no one was hurt by the trades in question 
and there were no financial losses by investors in the marketplace 
the settlement was made to avoid lengthy and costly litigation with 
the government lewis attorney theodore wells jr said 
during his guilty plea last august lewis admitted that he 
manipulated the stock price of the firemans fund in may 1986 on 
the same day american express co planned to sell to the public a 
large part of its stock in firemans fund 
lewis was implicated by west coast trader boyd l jefferies who 
said he helped in the firemans fund stock manipulation 
lewis was sentenced to three years probation and a 250000 
fine his former firm sb lewis amp co also pleaded guilty in the 
criminal case 
jefferies was sentenced to five years probation and a 250000 
fine 
